# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Vercel Speed Insights has been **successfully implemented** in this Next.js portfolio project.

## Implementation Status: ✅ COMPLETE

The Vercel Speed Insights package was already properly installed and configured in the project. No additional changes were required.

## What Was Found

### 1. Package Installation ✅
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights` v1.3.1
- **Status**: Already installed in package.json dependencies
- **Package Manager**: npm (using package-lock.json)

### 2. Configuration ✅
- **Location**: `src/app/layout.tsx` (root layout)
- **Import**: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- **Placement**: Correctly placed inside the `<body>` tag after the main content
- **Router Type**: App Router (Next.js 16.1.6)

### 3. Implementation Details

The implementation follows Next.js 13.5+ App Router best practices:

**File**: `src/app/layout.tsx`
```typescript
import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="id" suppressHydrationWarning>
      <body>
        <Providers>
          <TranslationProvider>
            <Navbar />
            <main className="flex-grow">{children}</main>
          </TranslationProvider>
        </Providers>
        <Analytics />
        <SpeedInsights />  // ✅ Correctly placed
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

